== Pesto Couscous ==

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{4} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a medium #saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add half the garlic and cook for ~{30%secs}.

Pour in the @water for the couscous{240%ml} and half the @chicken stock paste{20%g}. Bring to the boil.

When boiling, remove from the heat, stir in the @couscous{120%g} and pop a #lid{} on the pan.

Leave to the side for ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve.

== Chicken in Smashed Tomato Sauce ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until the chicken is golden brown on the outside, ~{5-6%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Stir the remaining garlic and @balsamic glaze{12%ml} into the pan until combined.

Carefully squish the tomatoes until they burst, then add the remaining chicken stock paste, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water for the sauce{75%ml}.

Bring the sauce to a simmer and reduce until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once thickened, remove from the heat and vigorously stir in the @butter{10%g} and half the @fresh pesto{32%g}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir the remaining pesto through the couscous and fluff up with a #fork{}.

Share the pesto couscous between your #bowls{}, then top with the chicken and smashed tomato sauce.

Crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} over the top to finish.

Enjoy!